physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Severe hypophosphatemia with serum phosphate level 0.4 mg/dL; fractional excretion of phosphate 34%; elevated FGF23 levels at 674 RU/mL.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Phosphate levels improved over time: 0.4 mg/dL at admission, 2.6 mg/dL after 5 weeks, and 3.8 mg/dL after 12 weeks. FGF23 levels decreased to 174 RU/mL after 5 weeks and 167 RU/mL after 12 weeks.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Immunohistochemical analysis indicated strong staining for FGF23 in the patient's adenocarcinoma.
